title: Did Danielle Armstrong just take a swipe at former TOWIE beau James Lock's new girlfriend Yaz Oukhellou?
text:
Celebs Did Danielle Armstrong just take a swipe at former TOWIE beau James Lock's new girlfriend Yaz Oukhellou? The former reality star seemed to take their growing feud to the next level with a cheeky Instagram post Share By JJ Nattrass Emmeline Saunders 14:35, 30 MAR 2017 Get celebs   Thank you for subscribing!   
They got into a epic war of words on Sunday night, following a night of drama on the latest series of TOWIE. 
And it would seem that Danielle Armstoring has taken her new feud with the show's latest arrival, Yaz Oukhellou, to the next level with a very public dig on Instagram. 
Seemingly taking aim at her ex boyfriend's new girlfriend, the 28-year-old former reality star posed in a provocative slogan tee-shirt, which read, "She couldn't beat me on her best day". 
Meow! 
The pair found themselves clashing after Danielle took BFF Georgia Kousoulou's side in argument between the two current cast-members - something Yaz didn't take too kindly to. 
And following a huge argument on Twitter it seems that Danielle has come out swinging, as the caption accompanying the image only seemed to assert the garment's message was directed at her new enemy. 
'Enough said,' she wrote simply, followed by a flaming emoji, a message that wasn't lost on her followers who were quick to come to the conclusion Danielle had just called out Yaz once-more. It would seem that Danielle Armstoring has taken her new feud with the show's latest arrival, Yaz Oukhellou, to the next level with a very public dig on Instagram (Photo: Instagram) 
"Ohhhh shots fired," wrote one fan, while another cheekily quipped: "Ohhhh brilliant!! Now to wait for the reply." 
The beef between the pair first started on Sunday when Dani, who dated James 'Lockie' Lock while on the show, became embroiled in a serious spat with Lockie's new girlfriend Yaz – and even accused her of only starting an argument to gain more followers. James Locke and Yazmin Oukhellou seen arriving at Faces nightclub in Essex in February (Photo: FameFlynet) 
Not content with THAT, Yaz accused Dani right back of stroking Lockie's back while Yaz was on a date with him. 
It started when Georgia Kousoulou tackled Yaz and Amber Turner on the show about their apparent problem with her, calling them "bitchy" and "fake" before slamming Amber for having a fling with Dan Edgar – the ex of her friend Kate Wright. 
And Danielle, who is currently not part of the cast, took to Twitter to praise Georgia for standing up for her mate and being loyal to her. 
But Yaz wasn't happy with Dani sticking her oar in and started retweeting less than flattering messages about Georgia and Dani. 
These somehow reached Dani's eyes and ears and she lashed out at Yaz in a sub-tweet, telling one of her fans: "She just needs followers babe let her. All love here." 
Yaz immediately hit back by accusing Dani of making a move on Lockie while he and Yaz were on a date at Essex hot-spot Sheesh. 
Dani immediately blocked Yaz, as evidenced by Yaz's screenshot, but that didn't seem to bother the newest TOWIE recruit. 
"I don't stir I tell the truth I kept my mouth shut about her behaviour but I've had enough now," she fired back. 
"I'm just confronting her as they bang on about saying it straight to their face but when it comes to it I get blocked." Yaz revealed Dani had blocked her after she accused her of stroking Lockie's back in a restaurant (Photo: @YazminOukhellou/Twitter) Danielle is now dating Daniel Spiller (Photo: WENN) 
In response to questions about the back-stroking incident, Yaz revealed: "She came up to say hi to me then kept waking past and doing it I ignored it and so did he. Yet I'm two faced." 
And just when the drama was dying down, Lockie fanned the flames by posting a quote on his Instagram and tagging his new girlfriend in it. Instagram 
"Silence says a lot more than you think," the quote said, and fans were quick to pile in with their opinions on the feud. 
"Bin her off Lockie she's bad news! Fame hungry and gonna cause you so much unnecessary drama," said one. Instagram 
"Your new bird is vile. You need to put her in a place and tell her that's not how a lady should act," wrote a second. 
And a third summed it all up by saying: "Getting involved in any drama isn't classy at all but unfortunately it's the job and that's what it's about, as a reality show." 
TOWIE returns on Wednesday at 10pm on ITVBe. Like us on Facebook
